TY  - JOUR
AU  - Srinivasan, Kandarp
T1  - The Securitization Flash Flood
PY  - 2026
Y1  - 2026/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfae027
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
SP  - 46
EP  - 85
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - This paper highlights a connection between the stability of a bank’s funding sources (debt claims) and the liquidity of assets backing those claims. Using a natural experiment and hand-collected data on over 5,000 repurchase contracts, the paper shows that a shock that increased the liquidity of private-label MBS resulted in a greater proportion of MBS financed on balance sheet by unstable funding sources (short-term repo debt). This finding is relevant to a recent banking crisis (the SVB collapse in March 2023) in which losses on a bank’s liquid assets led to a run by uninsured (“flighty”) depositors financing those assets. (JEL G2, K2)
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfae027
ER  - 




