AU  - Zhou, Frank S
T1  - Competition and Certification: Theory and Evidence from the Audit Market
PY  - 2026
Y1  - 2026/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfae023
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
SP  - 269
EP  - 303
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - We study how financial certifier competition influences loan contracting in the context of financial auditing. Exploiting the unexpected demise of Arthur Andersen that exogenously decreased auditor competition, we find a greater decrease in loan spread for borrowers in markets in which certifier competition declined more. Additional analyses suggest the result stems from enhanced audit quality and reduced credit risk. The effect of certifier competition is stronger for borrowers with weaker external monitoring and those generating significant revenue for their auditors. Our evidence highlights negative consequences of financial certifier competition. (JEL D43, G21, M42, M49)
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfae023
ER  - 




